&lt;h1 id="haters"&gt;Haters&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;January 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(I originally intended this for startup founders, who are often surprised by the attention they get as their companies grow, but it applies equally to anyone who becomes famous.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you become sufficiently famous, you&amp;rsquo;ll acquire some fans who like you too much. These people are sometimes called &amp;ldquo;fanboys,&amp;rdquo; and though I dislike that term, I&amp;rsquo;m going to have to use it here. We need some word for them, because this is a distinct phenomenon from someone simply liking your work.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>The Right Kind of Stubborn</title><link>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/persistence/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/persistence/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_zh/persistence/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
